< Review>
I needed to get an oil change for my car, and was a little hesitant at first to say the least upon reading the reviews posted here. I decided to just go to Jiffy Lube since it's supposedly an easy in, easy out experience and it was all that I expected.

It seems like they've stepped up their game since the last comments giving them very low stars. I got in, was immediately greeted and taken care of and within 5 mins was told that my specific car needed synthetic oil, which sucks for my wallet but having not done an oil change for the past 12K miles(yes, I know that's not good :p) I had to get it done. I was given an estimate about everything they were charging me for, no up selling or anything of the sort. 5/5 for now! Good place to go currently.<//Review>

<UserId.>109632977009246621219< /UserId.><name>Tim Gonzalez-Martin<//name><date>1555694930783</date><Rating>5<//Rating><text>Incredible diner & Friendly people! Ordered the Zee's Burger (pastrami, Swiss cheese, 1000 island dressing, all toppings) with Fries and coffee. The pictures don't lie, the burger is taller than the coffee cup. Made it a challenge to eat but very worth it. Pastrami was tasty on it own as was the beef patty. One of the best burgers I've had in years!
The waitress was very nice, brought extra napkins without prompt and even reminded me about the my to go box I was walking away from. She also clued me in to the lack of portion control. Shouldn't leave hungry from a diner. No danger of this happening here!
If you like diner food and environment check this place out for your next meal... assuming it Breakfast or Lunch, closes at 3p.<//text>< pictures>

< review>
I'd never been to Meea's but my couple friends are apparently regulars and love this spot for their Chicago-style with a veggie dog. I popped away from the uncomfortable argument and snuck in for 3 of the same, Chicago-style with a veggie dog. The orders took a few minutes and they loaded up the wieners with all the essential Chicago goodies. The buns here are more brat-style buns and not the typical Chicago poppyseed kind, but they're still good. My only tweak for next time is that I'd ask for extra sport peppers bc those are the best part, obviously.<//review>

<Response>None< /Response>< Text>
Really love to have Portal as an option that's literally 10min walk from where we live. I love coming here, seating on the community tables outside by the patio with a great view of the lake and exchanging sweet moments with your loved one and getting to know your neighbours!
Portal is exactly that, bringing people together. Love their indoors variety of seating by the tall tables, low tables and the lovely bar. Outside is great too with long community tables that easily accommodate 8-10 people and a lovely view of Lake Merritt :)

Prices are well balanced tho some dishes tend to get expensive like the carb loaded garbage bread priced at 18$, tho you get 4 big slices. I think the best way to go here is share the food since portions are quite generous. Love the choices on the menu. Impressed there were quite a few veg starters, salads and couple entres too.

We came on a Friday night at about 7ish and were quickly accommodated outside.
Between the two of us we shared plate of [6] hot spicy chicken wings and hot pastrami. Love the hot spicy sauce, it has the right amount of kick without being too spicy. The pastrami on rye was delicious, no mayo and whole grain mustard? YES!!! And love me their house made pickles. I make homemade pickles all the time so I can attest these were delicious!

All in all, we really had a great time and the bill only came to about 30 something $ for 2 plates and 2 beers which ain't bad I think. Service was on point and very friendly and efficient.

I haven't come yet for brunch here but dying to try :)<//Text>

Well, everything about this place is amazing. The wait is absolutely worth it...scheduling ahead and reserving a table is also absolutely worth doing as well! <user_id>105105764838344750907<//user_id><user_name>Aya Eano</user_name><time>1566489510539< /time><Rate>5</Rate>< Text>
Nothing like starting off your birthday was a birthday brunch and good company! I've been meaning to checkout Portal for a while and this was the perfect opportunity.
I was with a couple of friends, so we had our name on the Yelp Waitlist and waited roughly 15-20 minutes for a table. The outside seating is way nicer than the inside. It actually seems like a whole different restaurant and vibe. Brunch outside is even better!
We started off with a Pitcher of Grapefruit Mimosa (~$30). My friend and I were torn between getting a sweet or savory dish...so we got both! We shared the Stuffed Challah French Toast (~$14) and GCCB (~$15).
The Grapefruit Mimosa was super refreshing and tasted great. My one complaint was that it needs to be more chilled. Especially being that we sat outside, after a short amount of time, the mimosa started to get room temperature/borderline warm since it was a hot day.
The Stuffed Challah French Toast was great! It's super soft on the inside and a little crisp on the outside. The stuffing was delicious and overall, it wasn't overly sweet. I liked the fresh berries on top.
The GCCB was the real winner here! It was fried chicken on a buttery biscuit topped with mushroom gravy. It's also served with 2 eggs (any style, we got sunnyside) and deliciously crispy and soft potatoes. The potatoes were oddly addicting and the fried chicken was cooked well. They put a solid amount of gravy. It wasn't doused in gravy nor was it scarce. It was just right!
All in all, Portal is a solid brunch spot in the Oakland area. It's a short walk away from Lake Merritt which is very beautiful in the Summer. If you haven't been here yet, I recommend swinging by for a super satisfying brunch!< /Text>

Went here for late evening drinks and dinner with a group of friends and had a great experience. There is minimal indoor seating so if that's your cup of tea be prepared to wait. If you don't mind sitting outside (there are heaters and if your extra nice they may even provide you and your dining companions with blankets) just take a seat and order the delicious "Garbage Bread". My friends and I ordered the vegetarian option and were very pleased!
Overall great place, great service great food, great atmosphere.<//Text>

<user_id>102927846302779249017</user_id><user_name>Kimberly Stephenson<//user_name><Time>1561232931512<//Time>< Rating>
2</Rating>
< review>
Not really worth the hype.
At all.
They're flies constantly buzzing around the semi-outdoor kitchen, and little snowflakes of pollen constantly raining down in the outdoor dining area. The umbrellas helped, but only so much in the breeze. X.x
The flies were a tad uncomfortable to see, and it did make me question the sanitation, but the plates that kept coming out looked gorgeous, so I shrugged it off.
Even though we had a reservation, we still waited 15 minutes to be seated, watching at least 2 other walk-in couples get seated at the bar in front us.  How rude!
When we finally did get seated, we sat in the patio area. With the pollen snow aside, it was cozy enough-- there were long, picnic style tables & benches that were pretty sturdy... Would have been completely cosy if my husband & I weren't sharing the long table with half-dozen college age guys ... Not exactly the environment for a quiet date... X.x
I forgot to bring my ID, so indulging in a drink was out of the question. The staff was pretty strict, so my Husband allowed me a few sips of his 'Mr. Pickle' cocktail, which was nicely flavored.
My husband's steak and eggs were out of this world -- in the bites that he shared, the steak was cooked to perfection!

I ordered the Chileqiles with Carne Asada...
Compared to my husband's steak, the Carne was a complete joke.  It was literally cooked up ground beef -- the gritty texture was a dead giveaway.

When I doused the plate with all the included condiments, I almost forgot about the tasteless impostor Asada--  medley of crunchy tortilla chips & mushy scrambled eggs was pleasant enough. But for a $20 value, I was expecting wAy more from the meat... >.<

This isn't the place for a cosy, well-made brunch .. It's more for gatherings, and for simply-cooked food...

And inattentive staff.<//review>

< Text>
I really wanted to go here and like this place but the wait staff was rediculously rude.

I arrived here on a busy Sunday, the person at the counter asked for a name party size, and rudely mentioned it was 30-45 min wait. Being a lovely day I said we'd wait and they said they would text me.

We waited more than an hour till we found somewhere else, and we never got a response or anything from this place.

I don't care how amazing your French toast is (it looked really good), if you can't respond to people you want to give you money for food then you ought to revise your business model.< /Text>

<Pics>None</Pics>< text>
Delicious gastro pub. Good beer selections. Their burger is decadent. Also recommend the garbage bread (a sort of calzone) and quinoa sliders. Brunch menu is tasty, though perhaps for the bay area somewhat plain, and often there's a long (sometimes an hour!) wait for a table. Service is usually friendly, attentive, and quick. The outside seating consists of long wooden benches, which seat up to 10 or more people; often multiple parties share a bench. Nice views of the lake.< /text>

< user_name>
Jen H</user_name>
<time>1423210481779< /time><rate>4<//rate>< Text>
Cute brunch place by Lake Merritt!

I came here for a birthday brunch on Sunday and it was pretty packed. They have outdoor seating which is nice on a beautiful day. But it does get really really hot. I was sweating by the end of our brunch. The seating outside provides shade but not enough to cover you from the hot sun so dress lightly! They have bottomless mimosas during brunch :D and various beers on tap, so that can help you cool down!

I loved our waiter, Melvin! He was so awesome and he really made us feel at home. He also gave excellent recommendations for our group and kept us entertained. Definitely the service here was superb.

The Food:

Chilaquiles: I don't get this dish often, and this probably the second time I've had it. It was pretty good! I don't really have anything to compare it to but I did enjoy it. I thought the dish had good flavor but the chips were a little too soggy. I felt like the description of the dish on the menu was more appetizing than the dish itself. I don't know if I would get this again, it was good to try once.

Corned beef hash with 2 eggs any style: in the words of our waiter, "it is on point." Indeed it was, one of the best corned beef hash I've had. I really enjoyed it. He also recommended I got my eggs poached, which I did, and it was absolutely fantastic! The corned beef wasn't too salty and the potatoes balanced the dish, I would definitely come back again for this dish.

Overall, I thought this place was adorable. I would probably request to sit inside this time to avoid the heat. Perfect place to eat and then take a stroll around the lake :)<//Text>

<UserId.>105818373356803739204<//UserId.>< username>
Jiann Mok< /username>
<time>1426273218924</time>< Review>
Pros:
- GARBAGE BREAD (like a super classy calzone with chimichurri dipping sauce)
- brussels sprouts (soft with crispy outer leaves; slight sweet teriyaki flavor)
- cocktails are made with soju instead of vodka (I don't see this done often)
- quick service INDOORS (outdoors is a different story haha)
- friendly staff
- cool interior design/decor
- beautiful view from outdoors patio
- not difficult to find street parking (make sure you check street signs though!)

Cons:
- horrible service on outdoors patio (likely due to communal seat-yourself tables)
- chicken was juicy but bland in flavor
- ribs were smothered in a delicious sauce but were slightly dry/overcooked

Bottom line: Portal offers a great twist on classic American food. The garbage bread is a MUST TRY but I recommend that you sit indoors.< /Review>
